    "causal_summary": "The shared mk-spec-memory daemon is owned by one launcher. Phase 017 made that owner exit cleanly on disposal (no flap), but the daemon still dies with its owner: `shutdownLauncherForSignal` explicitly `child.kill(signal)`s the context-server. So every secondary session bridged to that daemon loses the backend for a few seconds plus a cold FTS rebuild until someone respawns it. This is the \"complete\" RC-2 fix the investigation deferred.",
